Presenting Problem / Chief Complaint: The patient expresses feelings of insecurity regarding their role as a part-time member of the band, indicating a desire for more recognition and security in their contributions.
History of Present Illness (HPI): The patient has been maintaining a gratitude journal, reflecting on positive experiences and little victories, which has led to a kinder self-perception. They have also practiced breathing exercises to manage anxiety, finding them helpful. However, they still struggle with feelings of inadequacy in their band role.
Therapeutic Interventions: The patient is interested in learning mindfulness and grounding techniques, which have been introduced during the session. They have practiced grounding exercises and found them beneficial.
Next Steps: The patient plans to incorporate grounding techniques into their routine, especially before performances, and aims to have a conversation with their bandmates about their feelings before the next session.
